   "source": [
    "# ``regionprops_3D``\n",
    "This is similar to the ``regionprops`` in ``scikit-image`` but has some extra features that are relevant to 3D images.  Note that the ``scikit-image`` version has been adding 3D capabilities, make the PoreSpy version less useful."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "42296990",
   "metadata": {

   "outputs": [],
   "source": [

    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import scipy.ndimage as spim\n",
    "ps.visualization.set_mpl_style()"

     "output_type": "display_data"

   "source": [
    "im = ~ps.generators.random_spheres(shape=[80, 80, 80], r=10, clearance=3)\n",
    "plt.imshow(im[20, ...], origin='lower', interpolation='none');"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9cc48e89",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We need to label each sphere so they are recognized as individual regions:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "a75c5b4c",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2022-04-25T01:54:54.339629Z",

    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"

     "metadata": {
      "image/png": {
       "height": 463,
       "width": 468
      }
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "regions = spim.label(im)[0]\n",
    "plt.imshow(regions[20, ...], origin='lower', interpolation='none');"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "d573de10",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {

    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "props = ps.metrics.regionprops_3D(regions)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e1349c01",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
